[3
Date: Tue 30 Oct 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: New York State Department of Health, W
est Nile Virus Update, 1 Jan - 29 Oct 2001 [edited
<http://www.health.state.ny.us/nysdoh/westnile/update/2001/today.htm>

Another West Nile Virus-positive Horse Reported in New York
-----------------------------------------------------------
On Mon 29 Oct 2001, the New York State Department of Agriculture and
Markets reported a new positive horse (Nassau County).
The total number of West Nile virus-positive specimens for New York
for the year [2001 is the following:
* 632 dead birds, 28 live birds [total 660
*255 mosquito pools
* 16 horses
* 12 humans.
County total West Nile virus-positive equine and human cases to date
are
the following: Mammals (16 horses); Nassau (3), Orange (1) and Suffolk
(12). Humans (12* cases); Nassau (4), NYC (6) [Brooklyn (2), Staten
Island (2), Queens (2), and Suffolk (1).
*One case occurred in a non-NYS Department of Health laboratory
worker. To protect confidentiality, county of residence is being
withheld.
As of Mon 29 Oct 2001, this report will be the last daily update until
next year. Updates will be provided weekly until next spring.
